                        "id": "0",
                        "type": "text",
                        "h": "#",
                        "t": "RedEye is an open source C++ 3D Game Engine developed from scratch by "
                    },
                    {
                        "id": "1",
                        "type": "link",
                        "h": "https://cumus.github.io/",
                        "t": "Ruben Sardón"
                    },
                    {
                        "id": "2",
                        "type": "text",
                        "h": "#",
                        "t": " & Julià Mauri. The engine counts with 15 integrated libraries including SDL2, OpenGL, ImGui, EASTL Wwise, and PhysFS. Our development process is featured at our Github repository together with our own-made website. After adding advanced procedures such as deferred shading and improved scene and resource handling, our latest version featured a particle pipeline with advanced lighting and collision physics. Check out our website for updated content and the engine's future plans."
